					Title: <b>0.8: How many times do I need to &quot;reindex&quot;?</b><br />
					Post by: <b>dree12</b> on <b>February 20, 2013, 03:48:10 AM</b>
					<hr />
					<div style="margin: 0 5ex;">I had a full blockchain before the upgrade. After the upgrade, 0.8 reindexed the blockchain once. That&#039;s fine, I thought. Not much time later, the number of blocks remaining went up by ~8000 and the last ~8000 blocks needed to be reindexed <i>again</i>. And now, the number of blocks remaining went up by ~3000 and the last ~3000 blocks need to be reindexed one more time. How many reindicies should I expect? Is this normal behaviour?</div>
					<br />
					<hr size="2" width="100%" />
					Title: <b>Re: 0.8: How many times do I need to &quot;reindex&quot;?</b><br />
					Post by: <b>grue</b> on <b>February 20, 2013, 02:59:19 PM</b>
					<hr />
					<div style="margin: 0 5ex;">afaik, you only need to reindex once. if you&#039;re having problems, you can always delete everything except for wallet.dat, and resync using 0.8</div>
					<br />
					<hr size="2" width="100%" />
					Title: <b>Re: 0.8: How many times do I need to &quot;reindex&quot;?</b><br />
					Post by: <b>dree12</b> on <b>February 20, 2013, 09:33:19 PM</b>
					<hr />
					<div style="margin: 0 5ex;"><div class="quoteheader"><a href="https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=145290.msg1542694#msg1542694">Quote from: grue on February 20, 2013, 02:59:19 PM</a></div><div class="quote">afaik, you only need to reindex once. if you&#039;re having problems, you can always delete everything except for wallet.dat, and resync using 0.8<br /></div><br />That&#039;s what I ended up doing after reindexing slowed to a block a minute. Turns out redownloading the chain isn&#039;t that bad anymore.</div>
					<br />
					<hr size="2" width="100%" />
					Title: <b>Re: 0.8: How many times do I need to &quot;reindex&quot;?</b><br />
					Post by: <b>Digigami</b> on <b>February 20, 2013, 09:36:01 PM</b>
					<hr />
					<div style="margin: 0 5ex;">Yeah I had to download the whole chain again, but this time complete download and verification took aprox 2.5 hours on a VM. Last time I went through that ordeal it was well in excess of 24 hours. The client certainly has come a long way with this most recent update. </div>
